HEADWORD: Cloche
<hw>Cloche</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., prop.,
bell.]</ety> <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>An apparatus used in
controlling certain kinds of a⟦eum⟧roplanes, and consisting principally
of a steering column mounted with a universal joint at the base, which
is bellshaped and has attached to it the cables for controlling the
wing-warping devices, elevator planes, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
